SIMPLE: recruit
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recruit
<hw>Re*cruit"</hw> <pr>(r?*kr?t")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Recruited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Recruiting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>recruter</ets>, corrupted (under influence of <ets>recrue</ets>
recruiting, recruit, from <ets>recro⟦icir⟧/tre</ets>, p. p.
<ets>recr⟦ucir⟧</ets>, to grow again) from an older <ets>recluter</ets>,
properly, to patch, to mend (a garment); pref. <ets>re-</ets> + OF.
<ets>clut</ets> piece, piece of cloth; cf. Icel. <ets>kl⟦umac⟧tr</ets>
kerchief, E. <ets>clout</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To repair by
fresh supplies, as anything wasted; to remedy lack or deficiency in;
<as>as, food <ex>recruits</ex> the flesh; fresh air and exercise
<ex>recruit</ex> the spirits.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her cheeks glow the brighter, <qex>recruiting</qex> their
color.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to restore the wasted vigor of; to renew in
strength or health; to reinvigorate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To supply with new men, as an army; to fill up or
make up by enlistment; <as>as, he <ex>recruited</ex> two regiments; the
army was <ex>recruited</ex> for a campaign</as>; also, to muster; to
enlist; <as>as, he <ex>recruited</ex> fifty men</as>.</def> <rj><au>M.
Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recruit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recruit
<hw>Re*cruit"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To gain new
supplies of anything wasted; to gain health, flesh, spirits, or the
like; to recuperate; <as>as, lean cattle <ex>recruit</ex> in fresh
pastures</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To gain new supplies of men for military or other
service; to raise or enlist new soldiers; to enlist troops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recruit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Recruit
<hw>Re*cruit"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A supply of anything
wasted or exhausted; a reenforcement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The state is to have <qex>recruits</qex> to its strength, and
remedies to its distempers.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically, a man enlisted for service in the
army; a newly enlisted soldier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recruiter</ent>⟦br⟧
